{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-05712/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-05712"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:57:12"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, pan, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man bends down to hug a seated woman."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-05712","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-05712"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/canvas/1/4a387f40-ffb3-4556-8b4c-282b828b6f36","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:56:28.916Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Ethan Warren notes the significance of spaces in <em>Phantom Thread</em>: “Anderson treats London in <em>Phantom Thread</em> much the way he treats Los Angeles in <em>Inherent Vice</em>. At no point is the viewer indulged with glimpses of Piccadilly Circus or St. Paul’s Cathedral, and while this may be another effort by the frugal Anderson to avoid ‘a waste of money, time, and feet of film,’ the blinkered view of the world around the House of Woodcock once again helpfully mirrors the characters’ state of mind. At the outset, we are chained to Reynolds’s workspace alongside the workaholic artist, and once Alma arrives, the close confines of the narrative world mirror her isolated condition as well” (Warren, <em>The Cinema of Paul Thomas Anderson</em>, 38–39).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05712/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:62.83021423358058,55.990834805660974,261.7044151376146,228.65538990825692"}}}]}]}]}